---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'allianz-care', text: 'Allianz Care', level: 2 },
  { id: 'axa-global', text: 'AXA Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'remote-worker-needs', text: 'Remote Worker Needs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'Remote Worker Insurance', href: '/best/remote-worker-insurance' },
  { title: 'Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', allianz: '€1M - €3M', axa: '€3M' },
  { feature: 'Visa Compliant', cigna: 'Yes', allianz: 'Yes', axa: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Home Country Cover', cigna: 'Optional', allianz: 'Optional', axa: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', cigna: 'Good', allianz: 'Best', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Telehealth', cigna: 'Included', allianz: 'Included', axa: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'App Quality', cigna: 'Excellent', allianz: 'Good', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Network Size', cigna: 'Largest', allianz: 'Large', axa: 'Large' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Best service', allianz: 'Best value', axa: 'Budget option' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', cigna: '$250-380/mo', allianz: '$150-220/mo', axa: '$140-200/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 40', cigna: '$350-500/mo', allianz: '$200-300/mo', axa: '$180-270/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', cigna: '$550-800/mo', allianz: '$350-500/mo', axa: '$320-460/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', cigna: '$900-1,400/mo', allianz: '$600-900/mo', axa: '$550-820/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Allianz vs AXA: Best Insurance for Remote Workers 2026"
  description="Compare health insurance for remote workers abroad: Cigna Global, Allianz Care, and AXA Global. Coverage for settled remote employees, not just nomads."
  headline="Cigna vs Allianz vs AXA: Remote Worker Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="For remote workers with a base abroad—not nomadic travelers. Comprehensive health coverage for those working remotely from a foreign country."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Best app and network. Unlimited coverage. Premium service for premium price.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Allianz Care</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Comprehensive coverage at 30% less. Best mental health benefits. Great for remote workers.</p>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Budget Option</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">AXA Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Lowest prices. Good coverage. Best for cost-conscious remote workers.</p>
      <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    Remote workers differ from digital nomads: you have a home base abroad, work for one employer (or yourself), and need real health insurance—not travel medical. All three insurers offer comprehensive coverage that meets visa requirements and provides genuine healthcare access.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best App</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Largest Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Unlimited</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global is the premium choice for remote workers who want the best service. The app makes managing care simple, direct billing is available at more providers than any competitor, and unlimited coverage means no surprises with serious illness.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Best mobile app for managing healthcare</li>
    <li>Largest provider network (1.5M+)</li>
    <li>Unlimited annual coverage</li>
    <li>Fast claims processing</li>
    <li>24/7 telehealth included</li>
    <li>Easy home country coverage add-on</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option (30-40% more)</li>
    <li>Mental health waiting period (24 months)</li>
    <li>Strict pre-existing condition handling</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Remote workers with good income who want premium service. Those who value convenience and the best digital experience.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="allianz-care">Allianz Care</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Mental Health</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Flexible</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Allianz Care offers the best balance for remote workers: comprehensive coverage at 30-40% less than Cigna. Mental health benefits are particularly strong—important for remote workers dealing with isolation. Flexible underwriting helps those with pre-existing conditions.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>30-40% cheaper than Cigna</li>
    <li>Best mental health coverage</li>
    <li>Shorter mental health waiting period (12 months)</li>
    <li>Flexible on pre-existing conditions</li>
    <li>Telehealth included</li>
    <li>Monthly payment available</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>€3M coverage limit (vs unlimited)</li>
    <li>Smaller network than Cigna</li>
    <li>App less polished</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Remote workers who want comprehensive coverage without premium pricing. Those prioritizing mental health benefits. Value-conscious professionals.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/allianz-care" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="axa-global">AXA Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Budget Option</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Coverage</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-amber-100 text-amber-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Europe Strong</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    AXA Global is the budget-friendly choice for remote workers who want real coverage at the lowest cost. Same comprehensive benefits, just with a smaller network and less polished experience. Especially strong for remote workers based in Europe.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lowest prices of the three</li>
    <li>Comprehensive coverage included</li>
    <li>Good mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Telehealth included</li>
    <li>Strong European network</li>
    <li>Good for families</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>€3M coverage limit</li>
    <li>Smallest direct billing network</li>
    <li>More reimbursement claims needed</li>
    <li>App less polished</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Budget-conscious remote workers. Those based in Europe. Families looking for affordable coverage.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/axa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Remote Worker Options"
    description="Get personalized quotes based on your work location and healthcare needs."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Remote workers pay for their own insurance (unlike corporate expats). Cost matters. AXA and Allianz offer significant savings over Cigna while maintaining comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for comprehensive coverage excluding US. Prices vary by age, health, and location.
  </p>

  <h2 id="remote-worker-needs">What Remote Workers Need</h2>

  <h3>Remote Workers vs. Digital Nomads</h3>
  <p>
    Key differences that affect insurance needs:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Location:</strong> Remote workers have a stable base; nomads move constantly</li>
    <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Remote workers stay years; nomads stay months</li>
    <li><strong>Visa:</strong> Remote workers often have residence visas; nomads use tourist/nomad visas</li>
    <li><strong>Healthcare needs:</strong> Remote workers need comprehensive care; nomads need emergency coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Visa Compliance</h3>
  <p>
    Most residence and work visas require health insurance. All three insurers provide:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Official coverage certificates</li>
    <li>Proof of coverage letters</li>
    <li>Coverage that meets visa requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Mental Health for Remote Workers</h3>
  <p>
    Remote work can be isolating. Mental health coverage matters:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Best—up to 50 sessions/year, 12-month waiting period</li>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good—20-30 sessions, 24-month waiting period</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Good—moderate limits, 12-month waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Telehealth Access</h3>
  <p>
    All three include telehealth, letting you consult doctors online. Useful for:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Quick consultations without clinic visits</li>
    <li>Access to English-speaking doctors</li>
    <li>Prescriptions for common conditions</li>
    <li>Mental health sessions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Home Country Visits</h3>
  <p>
    When you visit home (family, holidays, business), you need coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Full home country coverage add-on available</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz:</strong> Optional home country coverage</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Optional home country coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Have good income and can afford premium coverage</li>
        <li>Want the best app and digital experience</li>
        <li>Value fast claims and extensive direct billing</li>
        <li>Travel frequently for work</li>
        <li>Want unlimited coverage</li>
        <li>Prioritize convenience over cost</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Allianz Care if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want comprehensive coverage at better prices</li>
        <li>Prioritize mental health benefits</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Want shorter mental health waiting period</li>
        <li>Work primarily in Europe</li>
        <li>Value good coverage at fair prices</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose AXA Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Are budget-conscious</li>
        <li>Are based in Europe</li>
        <li>Can manage reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Have a family and need to manage costs</li>
        <li>Don't need unlimited coverage</li>
        <li>Want comprehensive benefits at lowest cost</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is SafetyWing enough for remote workers?</h3>
  <p>
    No. SafetyWing is travel medical insurance for nomads. Remote workers need real health insurance—comprehensive coverage that meets visa requirements, includes routine care, and provides genuine healthcare access. Cigna, Allianz, and AXA all qualify.
  </p>

  <h3>Does my employer need to provide insurance?</h3>
  <p>
    Depends on your arrangement. Remote employees of companies may have employer coverage. Independent contractors and freelancers typically need their own. Either way, verify your coverage meets visa requirements where you live.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I deduct insurance from taxes?</h3>
  <p>
    Often yes. Self-employed remote workers can usually deduct health insurance as a business expense. Check your specific tax situation—rules vary by country and employment type.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I work remotely from multiple countries?</h3>
  <p>
    International insurance covers you globally. Just update your primary residence country with your insurer if you move. Short trips to other countries are automatically covered.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need coverage in my home country too?</h3>
  <p>
    If you visit regularly, yes. Add home country coverage to your plan. Without it, you'll have gaps during visits—risky if something happens while visiting family.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Remote worker insurance needs vary by employment type, visa requirements, and location. Verify specific coverage terms with each insurer before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
